<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="356" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,656,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,765,791]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted as 
<taxonomicName box="[608,775,764,791]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="connected">race connected</taxonomicName>
to a specific habitat, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[212,347,801,827]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). This seems to be in disagreement with Hyllelberg (2004), who did not explicitly declare it infrasubspecific, but stated that “no evidence of subspecific status” occurs. Hyllelberg (2004) also listed 
<taxonomicName authority="Bellini, 1903" authorityName="Bellini" authorityYear="1903" box="[218,745,872,899]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="exiguum" variety="paludosum">
<emphasis box="[218,418,872,898]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Cardium exiguum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[471,594,872,898]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">paludosum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[600,745,872,899]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" pagination="20 - 27" refId="ref15673" refString="Bellini, R. (1903 a) I molluschi del Lago Fusaro e del Mar Morto nei Campi Flegrei. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, Series 1, 16, 20 - 27." type="journal article" year="1903">Bellini, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gmelin, 1791)" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[913,1350,872,899]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Parvicardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis box="[913,1168,872,898]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Parvicardium exiguum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin, J. F." box="[1182,1341,872,899]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" pagination="3021 - 4120" refId="ref17301" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1791) Caroli a Linne, systema naturae. Tom. I. Pars VI. Beer, Lipsiae, 1100 pp. [pp. 3021 - 4120]" type="book chapter" year="1791">Gmelin, 1791</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Taking into account the figure attached to its description (
<figureCitation box="[711,796,908,935]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1460,1485]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,395,1432]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,414,1432]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Bittium iadertinum var. coralligena. A. Original figures. B. Possible type material from Capri Island (Naples)—4.9×1.5 mm. C. Original label handwritten by Bellini. MCZR—not numbered. D, E. Murex trunculus var. propeconglobata. D. Fossil(?) shell from Sciacca (Agrigento)—72.4×52.8 mm. E. Original label handwritten by Monterosato. MCZR- M-7623. F, G. Fusus (Pseudofusus) pulchellus var. curta. F. Original figures. G. Shells from Capri Island (Naples) and original label handwritten by Monterosato (up to 16 mm in total height). MCCIC—drawer 8, n. 146. H. Clathromangilia granum var. prausi. Original figures. I. Left. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. minimum. Original figure. I. Right. Cardium (Parvicardium) exiguum var. paludosum. Original figures." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3449572/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
), as well as its peculiar shape, it constitutes a misidentification of a juvenile of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bruguiere, 1789)" authorityName="Bruguiere" authorityYear="1789" baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[405,879,944,971]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cerastoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="glaucum">
<emphasis box="[405,668,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Cerastoderma glaucum</emphasis>
(Bruguière, 1789)
</taxonomicName>
. On the other hand, it is also a primary homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bucquoy, Dautzenberg &amp; Dollfus, 1892" authorityName="Bucquoy, Dautzenberg &amp; Dollfus" authorityYear="1892" box="[181,956,980,1007]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cardium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Mollusca" rank="variety" species="edule" variety="paludosa">
<emphasis box="[181,348,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Cardium edule</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[402,505,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">paludosa</emphasis>
Bucquoy, Dautzenberg &amp; Dollfus, 1892
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1024,1092,981,1007]" name="France" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Corse</collectingCountry>
, also instituted on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[1300,1429,980,1007]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cerastoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="glaucum">
<emphasis box="[1300,1429,980,1007]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">C. glaucum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and thus permanently invalid (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[488,622,1017,1043]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 57). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[731,994,1016,1042]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cardiidae" genus="Cerastoderma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Veneroida" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="glaucum">
<emphasis box="[731,994,1016,1042]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="356">Cerastoderma glaucum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found again during samplings held in the area in 
<date box="[306,432,1053,1079]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" value="1978" valueMax="1979">1978–1979</date>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Russo, G. F. &amp; Ferro, R." box="[447,682,1053,1079]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref18911" refString="Russo, G. F. &amp; Ferro, R. (1980) Le biocenosi bentoniche del lago Fusaro. I-Osservazioni faunistiche. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, 89, 1 - 13." type="journal article" year="1980">Russo &amp; Ferro 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferro, R. &amp; Russo, G. F." box="[694,925,1053,1079]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" pagination="3 - 19" refId="ref17097" refString="Ferro, R. &amp; Russo, G. F. (1982) Le biocenosi bentoniche del Lago Fusaro. II-Malacofauna. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli, 91, 3 - 19." type="journal article" year="1982">Ferro &amp; Russo 1982</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<date box="[989,1115,1052,1079]" pageId="13" pageNumber="356" value="1975" valueMax="2018">1975–2018</date>
(authors’ unpublished data), and it constitutes one of the commonest taxa in the area.
</paragraph>
